comments: Butler (MIA) cleanly blocks Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) shot attempt before it touches the backboard.
Dort (OKC) is moving laterally into and initiates contact with Butler's (MIA) body after his gather, which affects the driving shot attempt.
Vincent (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Oladipo (MIA) contests the shot attempt near the rim and avoids making contact with Wiggins' (OKC) arm.
Williams (OKC) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Williams (OKC) legally contests Oladipo's (MIA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Butler (MIA) briefly grasps Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) outstretched arm and marginal follow-through contact occurs during his contest of the shot near the basket.
Vincent (MIA) makes clean hand on ball contact and dislodges it away from Williams (OKC) prior to any incidental follow-through contact as they pursue the loose ball.
Vincent (MIA) legally contests Giddey's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Cain (MIA) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Strus (MIA) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Wiggins' (OKC) shoulder, which does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.

Replay review of the foul called on Cain (MIA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Cain (MIA) turns toward Williams (OKC) and makes contact with his body after the release, which affects his ability to follow-through on the jump shot attempt.
Butler (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Wiggins (OKC) prior to incidental contact occurring.
Williams (OKC) turns his body and is not in a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Butler (MIA), which alters his play at the basket.
Butler (MIA) brings his hand toward Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during Gilgeous-Alexander's play on the perimeter.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.

From all available angles, it appears Vincent (MIA) swings the ball into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) leg as the ball gets cleanly dislodged. Any incidental contact as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
After review, it is confirmed that the ball is cleanly tied up with 0.8 seconds left on the game clock and a jump ball is correctly whistled between Vincent (MIA) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
Cain (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Muscala (OKC).
